<HEAD>Stocks Rebound, Dollar Edges Upward</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New throughout to UPDATE with closing dollar, stock prices.
EDITS to conform</NOTE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices rebounded in heavy afternoon trading,
while the dollar rose slightly in Tokyo trading Tuesday as dealers
awaited U.S. trade deficit figures.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues fell during the morning session but rebounded and
ended the day at 25,475.67 points, up 42.16 points, or 0.16
percent, from Monday's close.
   The dollar, after temporarily dipping below the 127-yen mark,
closed at 127.25 yen, up 0.02 yen from Monday's close.
   An exchange dealer at a major commercial bank in Tokyo, who
spoke on condition of anonymity, said the Tokyo market ``seems to
remain relatively calm'' until the release of U.S. trade figures
for January, scheduled for Thursday.
   Large-capital industrials and steels traded actively, but most
other sectors were quiet, according to an analyst who requested
anonymity.
