<TEXT>
   Sen. Lowell P. Weicker Jr., R-Conn., has
all but endorsed Vice President George Bush for the Republican
presidential nomination, saying that unlike the president, Bush
bases his decisions on facts and logic rather than ideology.
   Speaking to business leaders Monday, Weicker, who faces
re-election this year, also said the Republican presidential
campaign of Senate Minority Leader Bob Dole of Kansas has been
defeated.
   Weicker, a liberal Republican often at odds with President
Reagan and other conservatives, has has not made a formal
endorsement in the GOP presidential race but when asked, he
lavishly praised Bush.
