<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Lost Symphony,0135</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Newspaper: Lost Beethoven Work To Premier in London</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The first movement of Ludwig van
Beethoven's lost 10th symphony, reconstructed from drafts found in
West Berlin, will be premiered in London later this year, a West
German newspaper reported.
   The Bonn Express on Monday quoted Barry Cooper, a professor at
Scotland's University of Aberdeen, as saying the piece will be
performed in London at the end of the year.
   The newspaper did not give an exact date or location for the
performance.
   Cooper and Sieghard Brandenburg, the director of the Beethoven
Archive in Bonn, have said they found musical sketches and notes by
the composer.
   Cooper said the first movement, about 15 minutes long, was put
together based on the documents found in West Berlin.
</TEXT>
