<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--BoatRescue     03-15 0153</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Boat Rescue,0156</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Five Plucked From Sinking Boat</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GEORGETOWN, S.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Five men were pulled from a sinking boat
this morning about 50 miles into the Atlantic Ocean off Georgetown,
the U.S. Coast Guard said.
   The 54-foot-long Willie Victor, based in Murrells Inlet, radioed
the Coast Guard Monday night saying it was taking on water and a
Coast Guard helicopter was dispatched from Savannah, Ga., said a
Coast Guard spokesman in Miami.
   The helicopter arrived shortly after midnight and the men were
lifted into the helicopter after Coast Guard pumps could not save
the boat. The boat sank about 20 minutes later, the spokesmen said.
   The boat's owner and operator, Gerald Baston, suffered head
injuries, and another man, Tommy Morehead, suffered a broken leg,
the spokesmen said. The other men were identified as Neal Baston,
Art Ashworth and Dennis Barrios.
   The Coast Guard did not know the men's ages or hometowns.
</TEXT>
