<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--BoxingInjury     03-15 0162</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Boxing Injury,0167</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Marine Suffers Critical Injury During Championship Fight</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN DIEGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Marine amateur boxer was in critical but
stable condition today after he was injured during the Armed Forces
Boxing Championships here, officials said.
   Lance Cpl. Rickey Uzzel, 22, of Austin, Texas, was in the
intensive care unit at San Diego Naval Hospital, hospital officials
said this morning.
   Uzzel was under sedation and was stable after receiving therapy
to reduce pressure on his brain, said Lt. Pat Killy, hospital
spokeswoman.
   Navy and other military officials were not available for comment
Monday about the injury, a spokeswoman said.
   The Marine was knocked out Thursday during the
light-middleweight championship match with James Crisp, an Army
boxer who last fall was ranked eighth by the USA Amateur Boxing
Federation in the 156-pound class.
   The injury occurred during 23 seconds into the second round of a
three-round match.
   Last year, boxing matches here among recruits were stopped after
an 18-year-old died.
</TEXT>
