<2ND_LINE>PM-People-Keillor,0175</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>`Prairie Home Companion' To Get Limited Revival</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The news from Lake Wobegon is good today:
Garrison Keillor is bringing back ``A Prairie Home Companion'' for
a ``second annual farewell performance'' at Radio City Music Hall.
   ``It was so much fun leaving that we're coming back to say
goodbye again,'' Keillor said in announcing he would take to the
stage June 3 and 4.
   The second show will be broadcast on television by the Disney
Channel and on radio by the American Public Radio Network, which
broadcast Keillor's weekly show from Minnesota until he called it
quits last June 13.
   ``A Prairie Home Companion,'' featuring the fictional Minnesota
town of Lake Wobegon, had been on the air for 13 years.
   The reunion show will feature Butch Thompson, the pianist who
was a fixture on the show. It also will include guitarists Chet
Atkins and Leo Kottke, the Everly Brothers, singers Robin and Linda
Williams and the 1920s sound of Vince Giordano and the Nighthawks.
</TEXT>
