<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--BusAccident     03-15 0176</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Bus Accident,0181</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bus Crashes; 1 Dead, 12 Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOWLING GREEN, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A school bus carrying mentally
disabled passengers skidded off a road, killing a 6-year-old girl
and leaving 12 other people injured, officials said.
   The passengers _ nine children and three adults _ were on their
way home from the Wood Lane school and industries, part of the Wood
County Board of Mental Retardation and Development Disabilities,
when the accident happened Monday.
   Monica Roth of Northwood, who was sitting directly behind the
driver, was killed.
   The 11 other passengers and the driver were taken to Wood County
Hospital, where they were treated for cuts and bruises.
   Sgt. Al Vargo of the highway patrol said the driver couldn't
regain control of the bus after slipping off the side of the road.
   ``When she tried to bring her bus back on the roadway, she, for
some reason, lost control of the bus and it went back off the right
side of the road and overturned,'' he said.
   Vargo said the accident is under investigation.
</TEXT>
