<2ND_LINE>AM-Italy-Mobs,0161</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Arrest 15 Men in Mob Investigation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>REGGIO DI CALABRIA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police investigating murders
blamed on mob warfare arrested 15 men in raids that began before
dawn Tuesday in Calabria, a news agency reported.
   Prosecutors issued 24 arrest warrants for suspects on charges of
criminal association, Italian news agencies reported. By late
afternoon, police had served 15 of them, including three for men
already in prison.
   The ANSA news agency said that seven men were charged in two
murders last year in Villa San Giovanni, a town on the Calabrian
side of the Strait of Messina.
   Reggio Di Calabria province, the southernmost part of the
Italian mainland, has been bloodied by hundreds of murders linked
to the 'Ndrangheta mob in recent years.
   Investigators say mobsters are fighting among themselves for
control of lucrative construction and other public contracts in
underdeveloped Calabria, where the 'Ndrangheta is the local version
of the Sicilian Mafia.
