   The Teamsters union has set a new target of
March 29 for its 6,700 member flight attendants to strike Northwest
Airlines after getting a pledge that the carrier's mechanics and
baggage handlers will honor picket lines.
   ``Anyone who thinks they are going to fly Northwest during the
Easter holidays should forget it,'' William Genoese, director of
