   The commission and Justice Department reached the settlement
disclosed Monday with five manufacturers of the off-road vehicles,
which have been implicated in hundreds of deaths and thousands of
injuries in recent years.
   U.S. District Court Judge Gerhard A. Gesell will hold a hearing
