   ``Prices were under pressure most of the day,'' he said. ``There
was a little buying near the close and that lifted prices a little,
but there was no big feature today.
   On the close, wheat was \ cent to 1 cent higher with the
contract for delivery in March at $2.95{ a bushel; corn was { cent
lower to { cent higher with March at $1.98 a bushel; oats were 1{
cents to 3\ cents lower with March at $1.88{ a bushel; and soybeans
were 1\ cents lower to { cent higher with March at $6.13{ a bushel.
